{
  "texts": [
    "Granular predictions allow voters to fruitfully combine two well-known shortcuts: 'consensus cues' and 'group endorsement cues'.",
    "Recall that new polling methods can generate predictions for different demographic groups with an unprecedented level of precision.",
    "We have already explained that information about mass support of candidates generates 'consensus cues'.",
    "From a normative standpoint, this finding is ambivalent.",
    "On the one hand, we want to celebrate the incentive to think critically and to generate reasons."
  ]
}